Egypt Stocks: Amer Group and Orascom Construction Industries

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-07-04T13:18:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/egypt-stocks-amer-group-and-orascom-construction-industries.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30)  gained
0.2 percent to 5,428.1 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo, the
highest level since June 26.  The following shares rose or fell in Cairo. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Amer Group Holding (AMER)  , a real-estate and resorts
developer in Egypt, rose as much as 3.3 percent before closing
0.7 percent higher at 1.51 Egyptian pounds. Tourist arrivals in
the country increased 50 percent to 800,000 in April from the
previous month, according to the Cairo-based Central Agency for
Public Mobilization and Statistics.  Orascom Construction Industries (OCIC)   advanced as much
as 1.5 percent, before closing 0.9 percent higher at 274.3
pounds. The nation’s biggest publicly traded builder said it may
receive a $350 million investment from the International Finance
Corp.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
